a morte di Anna, con cui visse una brevissima storia d'amore, fece riconoscere a Scipio il senso e il valore, e quindi il compito, da dare alla propria esistenza: amare gli uomini e operare per il loro bene. Una nozione più ampia e inclusiva dell'amore, che trascende quello a due, dall'estate del 1911, ricambiato, per Gigetta, ch'egli sposò nel settembre del 1913, mentre a Elody continuò a legarlo un'amicizia vera e profonda, «provata su tutti i frangenti».  aThis volume presents the letters (approximately 600) that Scipio Slataper wrote between late 1909 and December 1915 to his "three friends" from Trieste, Anna Pulitzer, Gigetta (Luisa) Carniel, and Elody Oblath. These letters bring to light complex existential and intellectual storylines: of friendship, love, and pain, of the search of the purpose of life, cultural commitment, and artistic creation.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn Italian.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 4aBriefliteratur. 4aKulturgeschichte/Erster Weltkrieg. 4aScipio Slataper. 4aTriest. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / Italian.2bisacsh  aCultural History/First World War.  aLetters.  aScipio Slataper.  aTriest.1 aCaliaro, Ilvano, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCaliaro, Ilvano, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFavero, Marco, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aNorbedo, Roberto, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNorbedo, Roberto, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08